It is sometimes difficult to assess until to what point in time the numbers were collected. Over a week, it appears that there were 15 191 newly reported cases (20 979 the week before), averaging about 2170 cases PER DAY. At that rate, it would take about 30 days to reach one million cases, although the newly reported cases are decreasing. The low case fatality rate of 0.26 percent might suggest that some of the diarrhea may be non-cholera. There are now as many cases in over 6 months than in the entire 7 years of the Haitian cholera disaster. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5449946,126.]
